children.text: There is a visible hole in the waterproofing membrane in the shower, which could result in a long-term water leak that can cause damage to the structure and surrounding areas.
Part 3.8.1.2 of the Building Code of Australia (NCC/BCA) - Wet Areas, states that;
‘Building elements in wet areas within a building must-
a) be waterproof or water resistant in accordance with Table 3.8.1.1; and
Table 3.8.1.1 in the NCC/BCA shows that the shower area must be waterproofed;
These areas must be fully waterproofed to protect the building elements from damage in accordance with the BCA and Australian Standard 3740.
